ξ 39. a patre: the more usual preposition would be e instead of a. The father was L. Manlius Torquatus, consul with Cotta in ΒΩ. 65. Catiline conspired with Paetus and Sulla, who after election ‘to the consulship had lost their office through corrupt practices, in order to kil] Torquatus and Cotta; but the conspiracy was unsuccessful. After his consulship Torquatus obtained the province of Macedonia; in consequence of his exploits in his province, on the motion of Cicero, the senate conferred on him the title of imperator.
